#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr "Theravāda Collection on Monastic Law"

#. HTML: </p><p class="division">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr "Monks’ rules and their analysis"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:0.3"
msgid "Pārājikakaṇḍa"
msgstr "Monks’ Expulsion"

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:0.4"
msgid "Tatiya­pā­rāji­ka­sikkhā­pada"
msgstr "3. The third training rule"

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.1.0b"
msgid ""
msgstr "First sub-story"

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-cs-bu-pj3.1.1, pts-vp-en1.116, pts-vp-pli3.68, ms1V_376
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭā­gāra­sālāyaṃ."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Vesālī in the hall with the peaked roof in the Great Wood."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bhagavā bhikkhūnaṃ aneka­pariyā­yena asubhakathaṃ katheti,"
msgstr "At that time the Master spoke to the monks in many ways about unattractiveness—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.1.3"
msgid "asubhāya vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati,"
msgstr "he spoke in praise of unattractiveness,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.1.4"
msgid "asubha­bhāva­nāya vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati,"
msgstr "in praise of developing the mind in unattractiveness,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.1.5"
msgid "ādissa ādissa asubha­samā­pattiyā vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati."
msgstr "and in praise of the attainment of unattractiveness."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2, ms1V_377
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.1.6"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "The Master then addressed the monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.1.7"
msgid "“icchāmahaṃ, bhikkhave, addhamāsaṃ paṭisallīyituṃ."
msgstr "“Monks, I wish to go into solitary retreat for half a month."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.1.8"
msgid "Namhi kenaci upasaṅka­mi­tabbo, aññatra ekena piṇḍa­pāta­nīhāra­kenā”ti."
msgstr "No-one is to approach me except the one who brings me almsfood.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: paṭissuṇitvā → paṭissutvā (bj) | paṭisuṇitvā (pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.1.9"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti, kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paṭissuṇitvā nāssudha koci bhagavantaṃ upasaṅkamati, aññatra ekena piṇḍa­pāta­nīhāra­kena."
msgstr "“Yes, Venerable Sir,” they replied, and no-one approached him except the one who brought him almsfood."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3, ms1V_378
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.1.10"
msgid "Bhikkhū—“bhagavā kho aneka­pariyā­yena asubhakathaṃ katheti, asubhāya vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, asubha­bhāva­nāya vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, ādissa ādissa asubha­samā­pattiyā vaṇṇaṃ bhāsatī”ti,"
msgstr "The monks thought, “The Master has talked in many ways about unattractiveness,”"

#. VAR: te → atirekapāṭhena bhavitabbaṃ. evamuparipi īdisesu
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.1.11"
msgid "te anekākā­ra­vokāraṃ asubha­bhāva­nā­nuyoga­manu­yuttā viharanti."
msgstr "and they devoted themselves to the development of the mind in unattractiveness in its many different aspects."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.1.12"
msgid "Te sakena kāyena aṭṭīyanti harāyanti jigucchanti."
msgstr "As a consequence, they became troubled by their own bodies, ashamed of them, disgusted with them."

#. REF: pts-vp-en1.117
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.1.13"
msgid "Seyyathāpi nāma itthī vā puriso vā daharo yuvā maṇḍa­na­kajā­tiko sīsaṃnhāto ahikuṇapena vā kukku­ra­kuṇa­pena vā ­manus­sa­kuṇa­pena vā kaṇṭhe āsattena aṭṭīyeyya harāyeyya jiguccheyya;"
msgstr "Just as a young woman or man—someone fond of adornments, who had just washed her hair—would be ashamed, humiliated, and disgusted if the carcase of a snake, a dog, or a man were hung around her neck,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.1.14"
msgid "evameva te bhikkhū sakena kāyena aṭṭīyantā harāyantā jigucchantā attanāpi attānaṃ jīvitā voropenti,"
msgstr "just so those monks were troubled by their own bodies. They took their own lives,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.1.15"
msgid "aññamaññampi jīvitā voropenti,"
msgstr "took the lives of one another,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.1.16"
msgid "migalaṇḍikampi samaṇakuttakaṃ upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vadanti—"
msgstr "and they approached Migalaṇḍika, the ascetic lookalike, and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.1.17"
msgid "“sādhu no, āvuso, jīvitā voropehi."
msgstr "“Please kill us."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.1.18"
msgid "Idaṃ te pattacīvaraṃ bhavissatī”ti."
msgstr "This bowl and these robe will be yours.”"

#. VAR: lohitakaṃ → lohitagataṃ (pts1, mr)
#. REF: pts-vp-en1.118,  
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.1.19"
msgid "Atha kho migalaṇḍiko samaṇakuttako pattacīvarehi bhaṭo sambahule bhikkhū jīvitā voropetvā lohitakaṃ asiṃ ādāya yena vaggumudā nadī tenupasaṅkami."
msgstr "And hired for a bowl and robes, Migalaṇḍika killed many monks."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4, ms1V_379
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.1.20"
msgid "Atha kho migalaṇḍikassa samaṇa­kutta­kassa lohitakaṃ taṃ asiṃ dhovantassa ahudeva kukkuccaṃ ahu vippaṭisāro—"
msgstr "He took his blood-stained knife to the river Vaggumudā, and while he was washing it, he became anxious and remorseful:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.1.21"
msgid "“alābhā vata me, na vata me lābhā; dulladdhaṃ vata me, na vata me suladdhaṃ."
msgstr "“This is truly bad for me;"

#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.69
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.1.22"
msgid "Bahuṃ vata mayā apuññaṃ pasutaṃ, yohaṃ bhikkhū sīlavante kalyāṇadhamme jīvitā voropesin”ti."
msgstr "I’ve made much demerit by killing virtuous monks.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.1.23"
msgid "Atha kho aññatarā mārakāyikā devatā abhijjamāne udake āgantvā migalaṇḍikaṃ samaṇakuttakaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "Then, walking across the water, a god from the realm of the lord of death said to Migalaṇḍika,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.1.24"
msgid "“sādhu sādhu, sappurisa, lābhā te, sappurisa, suladdhaṃ te, sappurisa."
msgstr "“Well done, superior man, you’re truly fortunate."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.1.25"
msgid "Bahuṃ tayā, sappurisa, puññaṃ pasutaṃ, yaṃ tvaṃ atiṇṇe tāresī”ti."
msgstr "You’ve made much merit, because you’ve brought across those who hadn’t yet crossed.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5, pts-vp-en1.119, ms1V_380
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.1.26"
msgid "Atha kho migalaṇḍiko samaṇakuttako—"
msgstr "And Migalaṇḍika thought,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.1.27"
msgid "tiṇhaṃ asiṃ ādāya vihārena vihāraṃ pariveṇena pariveṇaṃ upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vadeti—"
msgstr "“So it seems that I’m fortunate and that I’ve made much merit.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.1.28"
msgid "tiṇhaṃ asiṃ ādāya vihārena vihāraṃ pariveṇena pariveṇaṃ upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vadeti—"
msgstr "He then went from dwelling to dwelling, from precincts to precincts, and said, “Who hasn’t crossed yet?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.1.29"
msgid "“ko atiṇṇo, kaṃ tāremī”ti?"
msgstr "Whom do I bring across?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.1.30"
msgid "Tattha ye te bhikkhū avītarāgā tesaṃ tasmiṃ samaye hotiyeva bhayaṃ hoti chambhitattaṃ hoti lomahaṃso."
msgstr "The monks who still had sensual desire became fearful and terrified, with their hair standing on end."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.1.31"
msgid "Ye pana te bhikkhū vītarāgā tesaṃ tasmiṃ samaye na hoti bhayaṃ na hoti chambhitattaṃ na hoti lomahaṃso."
msgstr "Only those who were free from desires were unaffected."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6, ms1V_381
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.1.32"
msgid "Atha kho migalaṇḍiko samaṇakuttako ekampi bhikkhuṃ ekāhena jīvitā voropesi, dvepi bhikkhū ekāhena jīvitā voropesi, tayopi bhikkhū ekāhena jīvitā voropesi, cattāropi bhikkhū ekāhena jīvitā voropesi, pañcapi bhikkhū ekāhena jīvitā voropesi, dasapi bhikkhū ekāhena jīvitā voropesi, vīsampi bhikkhū ekāhena jīvitā voropesi, tiṃsampi bhikkhū ekāhena jīvitā voropesi, cattālīsampi bhikkhū ekāhena jīvitā voropesi, paññāsampi bhikkhū ekāhena jīvitā voropesi, saṭṭhimpi bhikkhū ekāhena jīvitā voropesi."
msgstr "Then, on a single day, Migalaṇḍika killed one monk, two monks, three, four, five, ten, twenty, thirty, forty, fifty, even sixty monks."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7, pts-cs-bu-pj3.1.2, ms1V_382
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.2.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā tassa addhamāsassa accayena paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ āmantesi—"
msgstr "At the end of that half-month, the Master came out of seclusion and said to Venerable Ānanda,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.2.2"
msgid "“kiṃ nu kho, ānanda, tanubhūto viya bhikkhusaṃgho”ti?"
msgstr "“Ānanda, why is the Order of monks so diminished?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-en1.120, pts-vp-pli3.70
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.2.3"
msgid "“Tathā hi pana, bhante, bhagavā bhikkhūnaṃ aneka­pariyā­yena asubhakathaṃ katheti, asubhāya vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, asubha­bhāva­nāya vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, ādissa ādissa asubha­samā­pattiyā vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati."
msgstr "Ānanda told him what had happened and added,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.2.4"
msgid "Te ca, bhante, bhikkhū—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.2.5"
msgid "‘bhagavā kho aneka­pariyā­yena asubhakathaṃ katheti, asubhāya vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, asubha­bhāva­nāya vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, ādissa ādissa asubha­samā­pattiyā vaṇṇaṃ bhāsatī’ti, te anekākā­ra­vokāraṃ asubha­bhāva­nā­nuyoga­manu­yuttā viharanti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.2.6"
msgid "Te sakena kāyena aṭṭīyanti harāyanti jigucchanti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.2.7"
msgid "Seyyathāpi nāma itthī vā puriso vā daharo yuvā maṇḍa­na­kajā­tiko sīsaṃnhāto ahikuṇapena vā kukku­ra­kuṇa­pena vā ­manus­sa­kuṇa­pena vā kaṇṭhe āsattena aṭṭīyeyya harāyeyya jiguccheyya;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.2.8"
msgid "evameva te bhikkhū sakena kāyena aṭṭīyantā harāyantā jigucchantā attanāpi attānaṃ jīvitā voropenti, aññamaññampi jīvitā voropenti, migalaṇḍikampi samaṇakuttakaṃ upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vadanti—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.2.9"
msgid "‘sādhu no, āvuso, jīvitā voropehi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.2.10"
msgid "Idaṃ te pattacīvaraṃ bhavissatī’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.2.11"
msgid "Atha kho, bhante, migalaṇḍiko samaṇakuttako pattacīvarehi bhaṭo ekampi bhikkhuṃ ekāhena jīvitā voropesi … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.2.12"
msgid "saṭṭhimpi bhikkhū ekāhena jīvitā voropesi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.2.13"
msgid "Sādhu, bhante, bhagavā aññaṃ pariyāyaṃ ācikkhatu yathāyaṃ bhikkhusaṃgho aññāya saṇṭhaheyyā”ti."
msgstr "“Venerable Sir, please give another instruction so that the Order of monks may become established in final knowledge.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.2.14"
msgid "“Tenahānanda, yāvatikā bhikkhū vesāliṃ upanissāya viharanti te sabbe upaṭṭhā­na­sālā­yaṃ sannipātehī”ti."
msgstr "“Well then, Ānanda, bring together in the assembly-hall all the monks who live near Vesālī.”"

#. REF: pts-vp-en1.121
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.2.15"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti,"
msgstr "“Yes.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.2.16"
msgid "kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paṭissuṇitvā yāvatikā bhikkhū vesāliṃ upanissāya viharanti te sabbe upaṭṭhā­na­sālā­yaṃ sannipātetvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "When he had done so, he approached the Master"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.2.17"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.2.18"
msgid "“sannipatito, bhante, bhikkhusaṃgho;"
msgstr "“Venerable Sir, the Order of monks is assembled."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.2.19"
msgid "yassadāni, bhante, bhagavā kālaṃ maññatī”ti."
msgstr "Please do as you think is appropriate.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8, ms1V_383
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.2.20"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā yena upaṭṭhānasālā tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "The Master then went to the assembly-hall,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.2.21"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi."
msgstr "sat down on the prepared seat,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.2.22"
msgid "Nisajja kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "and addressed the monks:"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9, pts-cs-bu-pj3.1.3, ms1V_384
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.3.1"
msgid "“Ayampi kho, bhikkhave, ānā­pā­nassa­ti­samā­dhi bhāvito bahulīkato santo ceva paṇīto ca asecanako ca sukho ca vihāro uppannuppanne ca pāpake akusale dhamme ṭhānaso antaradhāpeti vūpasameti."
msgstr "“Monks, when stillness by mindfulness of breathing is developed and cultivated, it is peaceful and sublime, a satisfying state of bliss. And it stops and settles bad, unwholesome qualities on the spot, whenever they arise."

#. VAR: uhataṃ → ūhataṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.3.2"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, gimhānaṃ pacchime māse uhataṃ rajojallaṃ tamenaṃ mahāakālamegho ṭhānaso antaradhāpeti vūpasameti;"
msgstr "Just as a great, unseasonal storm in the last month of the hot season stops and settles the dust and dirt in the air,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.3.3"
msgid "evameva kho, bhikkhave, ānā­pā­nassa­ti­samā­dhi bhāvito bahulīkato santo ceva paṇīto ca asecanako ca sukho ca vihāro uppannuppanne ca pāpake akusale dhamme ṭhānaso antaradhāpeti vūpasameti."
msgstr "just so, when stillness by mindfulness of breathing is developed and cultivated, it is peaceful and sublime, and it stops and settles bad, unwholesome qualities on the spot, whenever they arise."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10, ms1V_385
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.3.4"
msgid "Kathaṃ bhāvito ca, bhikkhave, ānā­pā­nassa­ti­samā­dhi kathaṃ bahulīkato santo ceva paṇīto ca asecanako ca sukho ca vihāro uppannuppanne ca pāpake akusale dhamme ṭhānaso antaradhāpeti vūpasameti?"
msgstr "And how is stillness by mindfulness of breathing developed and cultivated in this way?"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-en1.122
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.3.5"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu araññagato vā rukkhamūlagato vā suññāgāragato vā nisīdati pallaṅkaṃ ābhujitvā ujuṃ kāyaṃ paṇidhāya parimukhaṃ satiṃ upaṭṭhapetvā."
msgstr "A monk sits down in the wilderness, at the foot of a tree, or in an empty hut. He crosses his legs, straightens his body, and establishes mindfulness in front of him."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.3.6"
msgid "So satova assasati"
msgstr "Simply mindful, he breathes in;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.3.7"
msgid "sato passasati."
msgstr "simply mindful, he breathes out."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11, ms1V_386
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.3.8"
msgid "Dīghaṃ vā assasanto dīghaṃ assasāmīti pajānāti,"
msgstr "When he breathes in long, he knows it;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.3.9"
msgid "dīghaṃ vā passasanto dīghaṃ passasāmīti pajānāti."
msgstr "and when he breathes out long, he knows that."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.3.10"
msgid "Rassaṃ vā assasanto rassaṃ assasāmīti pajānāti,"
msgstr "When he breathes in short, he knows it;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.3.11"
msgid "rassaṃ vā passasanto rassaṃ passasāmīti pajānāti."
msgstr "and when he breathes out short, he knows that."

# NOTE: I have here translated _kāya_ as breath in accordance with the usage in the Ānāpānasati Sutta [](MN 118.24) where the breath is specifically said to be a body among bodies. This is also the commentarial explanation: “He trains, ‘I will breath in,’ producing knowledge of and familiarity with the beginning, the middle, and the end of the whole body of the breath.” (_Sakalassa assāsakāyassa ādimajjhapariyosānaṃ viditaṃ karonto pākaṭaṃ karonto “assasissāmī”ti sikkhati_; [](Sp.2.411.2).)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.3.12"
msgid "Sabba­kāyap­paṭi­saṃ­vedī assasissāmīti sikkhati."
msgstr "When breathing in, he trains in having the full experience of the breath;"

#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.71
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.3.13"
msgid "Sabba­kāyap­paṭi­saṃ­vedī passasissāmīti sikkhati."
msgstr "when breathing out, he trains in having the full experience of the breath."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.3.14"
msgid "Passambhayaṃ kāyasaṅkhāraṃ assasissāmīti sikkhati."
msgstr "When breathing in, he trains in calming the activity of the body;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.3.15"
msgid "Passambhayaṃ kāyasaṅkhāraṃ passasissāmīti sikkhati."
msgstr "when breathing out, he trains in calming the activity of the body."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12, ms1V_387
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.3.16"
msgid "Pītippa­ṭisaṃ­vedī assasissāmīti sikkhati."
msgstr "When breathing in, he trains in experiencing joy;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.3.17"
msgid "Pītippa­ṭisaṃ­vedī passasissāmīti sikkhati."
msgstr "when breathing out, he trains in experiencing joy."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.3.18"
msgid "Sukhap­paṭi­saṃ­vedī assasissāmīti sikkhati."
msgstr "When breathing in, he trains in experiencing bliss;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.3.19"
msgid "Sukhap­paṭi­saṃ­vedī passasissāmīti sikkhati."
msgstr "when breathing out, he trains in experiencing bliss."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.3.20"
msgid "Citta­saṅ­khā­rap­paṭi­saṃ­vedī assasissāmīti sikkhati."
msgstr "When breathing in, he trains in experiencing the activity of the mind;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.3.21"
msgid "Citta­saṅ­khā­rap­paṭi­saṃ­vedī passasissāmīti sikkhati."
msgstr "when breathing out, he trains in experiencing the activity of the mind."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.3.22"
msgid "Passambhayaṃ cittasaṅkhāraṃ assasissāmīti sikkhati."
msgstr "When breathing in, he trains in calming the activity of the mind;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.3.23"
msgid "Passambhayaṃ cittasaṅkhāraṃ passasissāmīti sikkhati."
msgstr "when breathing out, he trains in calming the activity of the mind."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.3.24"
msgid "Cittap­paṭi­saṃ­vedī assasissāmīti sikkhati."
msgstr "When breathing in, he trains in experiencing the mind;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.3.25"
msgid "Cittap­paṭi­saṃ­vedī passasissāmīti sikkhati."
msgstr "when breathing out, he trains in experiencing the mind."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.3.26"
msgid "Abhippamodayaṃ cittaṃ …"
msgstr "When breathing in, he trains in gladdening the mind;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.3.27"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr "when breathing out, he trains in gladdening the mind."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.3.28"
msgid "samādahaṃ cittaṃ …"
msgstr "When breathing in, he trains in stilling the mind;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.3.29"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr "when breathing out, he trains in stilling the mind."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.3.30"
msgid "vimocayaṃ cittaṃ …"
msgstr "When breathing in, he trains in freeing the mind;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.3.31"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr "when breathing out, he trains in freeing the mind."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13, ms1V_388
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.3.32"
msgid "Aniccānupassī …"
msgstr "When breathing in, he trains in contemplating impermanence;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.3.33"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr "when breathing out, he trains in contemplating impermanence."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.3.34"
msgid "virāgānupassī …"
msgstr "When breathing in, he trains in contemplating fading away;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.3.35"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr "when breathing out, he trains in contemplating fading away."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.3.36"
msgid "nirodhānupassī …"
msgstr "When breathing in, he trains in contemplating cessation;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.3.37"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr "when breathing out, he trains in contemplating cessation."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.3.38"
msgid "paṭi­nissag­gā­nu­passī assasissāmīti sikkhati."
msgstr "When breathing in, he trains in contemplating relinquishment;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.3.39"
msgid "Paṭi­nissag­gā­nu­passī passasissāmīti sikkhati."
msgstr "when breathing out, he trains in contemplating relinquishment."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc14, ms1V_389
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.3.40"
msgid "Evaṃ bhāvito kho, bhikkhave, ānā­pā­nassa­ti­samā­dhi evaṃ bahulīkato santo ceva paṇīto ca asecanako ca sukho ca vihāro uppannuppanne ca pāpake akusale dhamme ṭhānaso antaradhāpeti vūpasametī”ti."
msgstr "Monks, when stillness by mindfulness of breathing is developed and cultivated in this way, it is peaceful and sublime, a satisfying state of bliss, and it stops and settles bad, unwholesome qualities on the spot, whenever they arise.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc15, pts-cs-bu-pj3.1.4, ms1V_390, pts-vp-en1.123
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.4.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe bhikkhusaṃghaṃ sannipātāpetvā bhikkhū paṭipucchi—"
msgstr "The Master then had the Order of monks assembled and asked them:"

#. VAR: vadanti → vadenti (bj, s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.4.2"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhū attanāpi attānaṃ jīvitā voropenti, aññamaññampi jīvitā voropenti migalaṇḍikampi samaṇakuttakaṃ upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vadanti—"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that some monks have taken their own lives, have killed one another, and have said to Migalaṇḍika,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.4.3"
msgid "‘sādhu no, āvuso, jīvitā voropehi, idaṃ te pattacīvaraṃ bhavissatī’”ti?"
msgstr "‘Please kill us; this bowl and these robes will be yours’?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.4.4"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.4.5"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā—"
msgstr "The Buddha criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.4.6"
msgid "“ananucchavikaṃ, bhikkhave, tesaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ ananulomikaṃ appaṭirūpaṃ assāmaṇakaṃ akappiyaṃ akaraṇīyaṃ."
msgstr "“Monks, it’s not suitable for these monks, it’s not proper, it’s not worthy of an ascetic, it’s not allowable, it should not be done."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.4.7"
msgid "Kathañhi nāma te, bhikkhave, bhikkhū attanāpi attānaṃ jīvitā voropessanti, aññamaññampi jīvitā voropessanti, migalaṇḍikampi samaṇakuttakaṃ upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vakkhanti—"
msgstr "How could those monks take their own lives, kill one another, and say to Migalaṇḍika,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.4.8"
msgid "‘sādhu no, āvuso, jīvitā voropehi, idaṃ te pattacīvaraṃ bhavissatī’ti."
msgstr "‘Please kill us; this bowl and these robes will be yours’?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.4.9"
msgid "Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.4.10"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.4.10a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Preliminary ruling"

#. HTML: </h3><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc16, ms1V_391
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.4.11"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu sañcicca manus­savig­gahaṃ jīvitā voropeyya satthahārakaṃ vāssa pariyeseyya, ayampi pārājiko hoti asaṃvāso”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk intentionally kills a human being or seeks an instrument of death for him, he too is expelled and excluded from the community.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p class="endsection">
#. REF: sc17, ms1V_392
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:1.4.12"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Second sub-story"

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: sc18, pts-cs-bu-pj3.2, ms1V_393
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aññataro upāsako gilāno hoti."
msgstr "At one time a lay follower was sick."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.2"
msgid "Tassa pajāpati abhirūpā hoti dassanīyā pāsādikā."
msgstr "He had a beautiful and pleasant wife,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.3"
msgid "Chabbaggiyā bhikkhū tassā itthiyā paṭi­baddha­cittā honti."
msgstr "and the monks from the group of six had fallen in love with her."

#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.72
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.4"
msgid "Atha kho chabbaggiyānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—"
msgstr "They said to each other,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.5"
msgid "“sace kho so, āvuso, upāsako jīvissati na mayaṃ taṃ itthiṃ labhissāma."
msgstr "“If this lay follower lives, we won’t get this woman."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.6"
msgid "Handa mayaṃ, āvuso, tassa upāsakassa maraṇavaṇṇaṃ saṃvaṇṇemā”ti."
msgstr "Come, let’s praise death to him.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.7"
msgid "Atha kho chabbaggiyā bhikkhū yena so upāsako tenu­pasaṅka­miṃsu;"
msgstr "They then went to that lay follower"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.8"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā taṃ upāsakaṃ etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "and said,"

#. REF: pts-vp-en1.124
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.9"
msgid "“tvaṃ khosi, upāsaka, katakalyāṇo katakusalo katabhīruttāṇo akatapāpo akataluddo akatakibbiso."
msgstr "“You’ve done what’s good and wholesome; you’ve made a shelter against fear. You haven’t done anything bad:"

#. REF: pts-vp-en1.124
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.10"
msgid "Kataṃ tayā kalyāṇaṃ, akataṃ tayā pāpaṃ."
msgstr "you haven’t been greedy or immoral."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.11"
msgid "Kiṃ tuyhiminā pāpakena dujjīvitena."
msgstr "What’s the point of this wretched and difficult life?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.12"
msgid "Mataṃ te jīvitā seyyo."
msgstr "Death is better for you than life."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.13"
msgid "Ito tvaṃ kālaṅkato kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjissasi."
msgstr "When you have passed away, you’ll be reborn in a happy place, in heaven."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.14"
msgid "Tattha dibbehi pañcahi kāmaguṇehi samappito samaṅgībhūto paricāressasī”ti."
msgstr "There you’ll be able to enjoy the five kinds of heavenly sense pleasure.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc19, ms1V_394
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.15"
msgid "Atha kho so upāsako—"
msgstr "That lay follower thought,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.16"
msgid "“saccaṃ kho ayyā āhaṃsu."
msgstr "“The Venerables have spoken the truth,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.17"
msgid "Ahañhi katakalyāṇo katakusalo katabhīruttāṇo akatapāpo akataluddo akatakibbiso."
msgstr "for I’ve done what’s good and avoided what’s bad,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.18"
msgid "Kataṃ mayā kalyāṇaṃ, akataṃ mayā pāpaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.19"
msgid "Kiṃ mayhiminā pāpakena dujjīvitena."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.20"
msgid "Mataṃ me jīvitā seyyo."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.21"
msgid "Ito ahaṃ kālaṅkato kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjissāmi."
msgstr "and after death I’ll be reborn in a happy place.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.22"
msgid "Tattha dibbehi pañcahi kāmaguṇehi samappito samaṅgībhūto paricāressāmī”ti,"
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.23"
msgid "so asappāyāni ceva bhojanāni bhuñji asappāyāni ca khādanīyāni khādi asappāyāni ca sāyanīyāni sāyi asappāyāni ca pānāni pivi."
msgstr "From then on he ate various kinds of detrimental food and drank detrimental drinks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.24"
msgid "Tassa asappāyāni ceva bhojanāni bhuñjato asappāyāni ca khādanīyāni khādato asappāyāni ca sāyanīyāni sāyato asappāyāni ca pānāni pivato kharo ābādho uppajji."
msgstr "and as a consequence, he became seriously ill"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.25"
msgid "So teneva ābādhena kālamakāsi."
msgstr "and died."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.26"
msgid "Tassa pajāpati ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—"
msgstr "But his wife complained and criticized those monks,"

#. REF: pts-vp-en1.125
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.27"
msgid "“alajjino ime samaṇā sakyaputtiyā dussīlā musāvādino."
msgstr "“These Sakyan ascetics are shameless and immoral liars."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.28"
msgid "Ime hi nāma dhammacārino samacārino brahmacārino saccavādino sīlavanto kalyāṇadhammā paṭijānissanti."
msgstr "They claim to live according to the Truth, to be celibate and of good conduct, to be truthful, moral, and of good character."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.29"
msgid "Natthi imesaṃ sāmaññaṃ natthi imesaṃ brahmaññaṃ,"
msgstr "But they don’t have the qualities of an ascetic or a brahmin;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.30"
msgid "naṭṭhaṃ imesaṃ sāmaññaṃ naṭṭhaṃ imesaṃ brahmaññaṃ, kuto imesaṃ sāmaññaṃ kuto imesaṃ brahmaññaṃ, apagatā ime sāmaññā apagatā ime brahmaññā."
msgstr "they’ve lost the plot."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.31"
msgid "Ime me sāmikassa maraṇavaṇṇaṃ saṃvaṇṇesuṃ."
msgstr "They praised death to my husband,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.32"
msgid "Imehi me sāmiko mārito”ti."
msgstr "and because of them my husband has died.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.33"
msgid "Aññepi manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "And other people complained and criticized them in the same way."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.34"
msgid "“alajjino ime samaṇā sakyaputtiyā dussīlā musāvādino."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.35"
msgid "Ime hi nāma dhammacārino samacārino brahmacārino saccavādino sīlavanto kalyāṇadhammā paṭijānissanti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.36"
msgid "Natthi imesaṃ sāmaññaṃ natthi imesaṃ brahmaññaṃ, naṭṭhaṃ imesaṃ sāmaññaṃ naṭṭhaṃ imesaṃ brahmaññaṃ, kuto imesaṃ sāmaññaṃ kuto imesaṃ brahmaññaṃ, apagatā ime sāmaññā apagatā ime brahmaññā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.37"
msgid "Ime upāsakassa maraṇavaṇṇaṃ saṃvaṇṇesuṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.38"
msgid "Imehi upāsako mārito”ti."
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc20, ms1V_395
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.39"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ."
msgstr "The monks heard the criticism of those people."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.40"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "Those monks who had few desires and a sense of conscience, who were contented, afraid of wrongdoing, and desirous of training,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.41"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized those monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.42"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū upāsakassa maraṇavaṇṇaṃ saṃvaṇṇissantī”ti."
msgstr "“How could they praise death to that lay follower?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc21, ms1V_396, pts-vp-pli3.73
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.43"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū chabbaggiye bhikkhū aneka­pariyā­yena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing those monks in various ways, they told the Master …"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.44"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, upāsakassa maraṇavaṇṇaṃ saṃvaṇṇethā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you praised death to that lay follower?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.45"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.46"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā—"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.47"
msgid "“ananucchavikaṃ, moghapurisā, ananulomikaṃ appaṭirūpaṃ assāmaṇakaṃ akappiyaṃ akaraṇīyaṃ."
msgstr "“Foolish men, it’s not suitable, it’s not proper, it’s not worthy of an ascetic, it’s not allowable, it should not be done."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.48"
msgid "Kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, upāsakassa maraṇavaṇṇaṃ saṃvaṇṇissatha."
msgstr "How could you praise death to that lay follower?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.49"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.50"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.50a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. HTML: </h2><p>_Satthahāraka_. I here follow Richard Gombrich’s interpretation of this word. See, “The Mass Suicide of Monks in Discourse and Vinaya Literature,” by Analayo, Journal of the Oxford Centre for Buddhist Studies, 7: 11-55, 2014.<span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc22, pts-vp-en1.126
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.51"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu sañcicca manus­savig­gahaṃ jīvitā voropeyya satthahārakaṃ vāssa pariyeseyya maraṇavaṇṇaṃ vā saṃvaṇṇeyya maraṇāya vā samādapeyya—"
msgstr "‘If a monk intentionally kills a human being or seeks an instrument of death for him or praises death or incites someone to die, saying,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.52"
msgid "‘ambho purisa, kiṃ tuyhiminā pāpakena dujjīvitena,"
msgstr "“Good man, what’s the point of this wretched and difficult life?"

#. VAR: mataṃ te → matante (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.53"
msgid "mataṃ te jīvitā seyyo’ti,"
msgstr "Death is better for you than life!”—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.54"
msgid "mataṃ te jīvitā seyyo’ti, iti cittamano cittasaṅkappo aneka­pariyā­yena maraṇavaṇṇaṃ vā saṃvaṇṇeyya, maraṇāya vā samādapeyya,"
msgstr "thinking and intending thus, if he praises death in various ways or incites someone to die—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:2.55"
msgid "ayampi pārājiko hoti asaṃvāso”ti."
msgstr "he too is expelled and excluded from the community.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc23, pts-cs-bu-pj3.3, ms1V_398
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:3.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:3.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. HTML: </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:3.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:3.4"
msgid "… pe … ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc24, ms1V_399
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:3.5"
msgid "Sañciccāti"
msgstr "Intentionally:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:3.6"
msgid "jānanto sañjānanto cecca abhivitaritvā vītikkamo."
msgstr "knowing, perceiving, having intended, having decided, he transgresses."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc25, ms1V_400
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:3.7"
msgid "Manussaviggaho nāma"
msgstr "A human being:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:3.8"
msgid "yaṃ mātukucchismiṃ paṭhamaṃ cittaṃ uppannaṃ paṭhamaṃ viññāṇaṃ pātubhūtaṃ, yāva maraṇakālā etthantare eso manussaviggaho nāma."
msgstr "from the mind’s first appearance in a mother’s womb, from the first manifestation of consciousness, until the time of death: in between these—this is called “a human being.”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc26, ms1V_401
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:3.9"
msgid "Jīvitā voropeyyāti"
msgstr "Kills:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:3.10"
msgid "jīvitindriyaṃ upacchindati uparodheti santatiṃ vikopeti."
msgstr "Cuts off the life faculty, brings it to an end, interrupts its continuation."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc27, ms1V_402
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:3.11"
msgid "Satthahārakaṃ vāssa pariyeseyyāti"
msgstr "Or seeks an instrument of death for him:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
#. VAR: bheṇḍiṃ vā → bhendiṃ vā (mr)
#. VAR: laguḷaṃ vā → lagulaṃ (si) | sūlaṃ vā laguḷaṃ vā (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:3.12"
msgid "asiṃ vā sattiṃ vā bheṇḍiṃ vā laguḷaṃ vā pāsāṇaṃ vā satthaṃ vā visaṃ vā rajjuṃ vā."
msgstr "a sword, a dagger, an arrow, a club, a rock, a knife, poison, or a rope."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc28, pts-vp-en1.127, ms1V_403
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:3.13"
msgid "Maraṇavaṇṇaṃ vā saṃvaṇṇeyyāti"
msgstr "Or praises death:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:3.14"
msgid "jīvite ādīnavaṃ dasseti, maraṇe vaṇṇaṃ bhaṇati."
msgstr "he shows the disadvantage in living and speaks in praise of death."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc29, ms1V_404
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:3.15"
msgid "Maraṇāya vā samādapeyyāti"
msgstr "Or incites someone to die:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:3.16"
msgid "satthaṃ vā āhara, visaṃ vā khāda, rajjuyā vā ubbandhitvā kālaṃ karohīti."
msgstr "he says, “Kill yourself with a knife/eat poison/die by hanging yourself with a rope.”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc30, ms1V_405
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:3.17"
msgid "Ambho purisāti"
msgstr "Good man:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:3.18"
msgid "ālapa­nādhi­vacana­metaṃ."
msgstr "this is a form of address."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc31, ms1V_406
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:3.19"
msgid "Kiṃ tuyhiminā pāpakena dujjīvitenāti"
msgstr "What’s the point of this wretched and difficult life:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:3.20"
msgid "pāpakaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Wretched life:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:3.21"
msgid "jīvitaṃ aḍḍhānaṃ jīvitaṃ upādāya daliddānaṃ jīvitaṃ pāpakaṃ lāmakaṃ,"
msgstr "the life of the poor is wretched compared to the life of the rich;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:3.22"
msgid "sadhanānaṃ jīvitaṃ upādāya adhanānaṃ jīvitaṃ pāpakaṃ,"
msgstr "the life of the impoverished is wretched compared to the life of the wealthy;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:3.23"
msgid "devānaṃ jīvitaṃ upādāya manussānaṃ jīvitaṃ pāpakaṃ."
msgstr "the life of humans is wretched compared to the life of the gods."

#. HTML: </span></span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc32, pts-vp-pli3.74, ms1V_407
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:3.24"
msgid "Dujjīvitaṃ nāma "
msgstr "Difficult life:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:3.25"
msgid "hatthac­chin­nassa pādacchinnassa ­hattha­pādac­chinnassa kaṇṇac­chin­nassa nāsacchinnassa ­kaṇṇanā­sacchin­nassa,"
msgstr "the life of one whose hands are cut off, whose feet are cut off, whose hands and feet are cut off, whose ears are cut off, whose nose is cut off, whose ears and nose are cut off."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:3.26"
msgid "iminā ca pāpakena iminā ca dujjīvitena mataṃ te jīvitā seyyoti."
msgstr "Because of this sort of wretchedness and because of this sort of difficult life, one says, “Death is better for you than life.”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc33, ms1V_408
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:3.27"
msgid "Iti cittamanoti"
msgstr "Thinking:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:3.28"
msgid "yaṃ cittaṃ taṃ mano, yaṃ mano taṃ cittaṃ."
msgstr "mind and thought are equivalent."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc34, ms1V_409
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:3.29"
msgid "Cittasaṅkappoti"
msgstr "Intending:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:3.30"
msgid "maraṇasaññī maraṇacetano maraṇādhippāyo."
msgstr "perceiving death, intending death, aiming at death."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc35, ms1V_410
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:3.31"
msgid "Aneka­pariyā­yenāti"
msgstr "In various ways:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:3.32"
msgid "uccāvacehi ākārehi."
msgstr "in different manners."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc36, ms1V_411
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:3.33"
msgid "Maraṇavaṇṇaṃ vā saṃvaṇṇeyyāti"
msgstr "He praises death:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:3.34"
msgid "jīvite ādīnavaṃ dasseti, maraṇe vaṇṇaṃ bhaṇati—"
msgstr "he shows the disadvantage in living and speaks in praise of death, saying,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:3.35"
msgid "“ito tvaṃ kālaṅkato kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjissasi,"
msgstr "“When you’ve passed away, with the break-up of the body after death, you’ll be reborn in a happy destination, in a heaven world."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:3.36"
msgid "tattha dibbehi pañcahi kāmaguṇehi samappito samaṅgībhūto paricāressasī”ti."
msgstr "There you’ll have access to and enjoy the five kinds of heavenly sense pleasures.”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc37, ms1V_412
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:3.37"
msgid "Maraṇāya vā samādapeyyāti"
msgstr "Or incites someone to die:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:3.38"
msgid "satthaṃ vā āhara, visaṃ vā khāda, rajjuyā vā ubbandhitvā kālaṃ karohi, sobbhe vā narake vā papāte vā papatāti."
msgstr "he says, “Kill yourself with a knife/eat poison/die by hanging yourself with a rope/jump into a chasm/jump into a pit/jump off a cliff.”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc38, ms1V_413
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:3.39"
msgid "Ayampīti"
msgstr "He too:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:3.40"
msgid "purime upādāya vuccati."
msgstr "this is said with reference to the preceding offenses entailing expulsion."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc39, ms1V_414
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:3.41"
msgid "Pārājiko hotīti"
msgstr "Is expelled:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
#. VAR: dvidhā bhinnā → dvedhā bhinnā (bj, s1-3, pts1)
#. REF: pts-vp-en1.128
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:3.42"
msgid "seyyathāpi nāma puthusilā dvidhā bhinnā appaṭisandhikā hoti,"
msgstr "just as an ordinary stone that has been broken in half cannot be put back together again,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:3.43"
msgid "evameva bhikkhu sañcicca manus­savig­gahaṃ jīvitā voropetvā assamaṇo hoti asakyaputtiyo."
msgstr "so too a monk who has intentionally killed a human being is not an ascetic, not a son of the Sakyan—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:3.44"
msgid "Tena vuccati—"
msgstr "therefore it is said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:3.45"
msgid "“pārājiko hotī”ti."
msgstr "“he is expelled.”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc40, ms1V_415
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:3.46"
msgid "Asaṃvāsoti"
msgstr "Excluded from the community:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:3.47"
msgid "saṃvāso nāma"
msgstr "Community:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:3.48"
msgid "ekakammaṃ ekuddeso samasikkhatā—"
msgstr "common procedures, the same recital, the same training—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:3.49"
msgid "eso saṃvāso nāma."
msgstr "this is called “community.”"

#. HTML: </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:3.50"
msgid "So tena saddhiṃ natthi,"
msgstr "He does not take part in this—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:3.51"
msgid "tena vuccati asaṃvāsoti."
msgstr "therefore it is called “excluded from the community.”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. HTML: </h2><h4>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.1.0b"
msgid ""
msgstr "Summary"

#. HTML: </h4><p>
#. REF: sc41, pts-cs-bu-pj3.4.1, ms1V_416
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.1.1"
msgid "Sāmaṃ, adhiṭṭhāya, dūtena, dūta­param­parāya, visakkiyena dūtena, gatapaccā­gatena dūtena,"
msgstr "Oneself, having resolved, by messenger, by a series of messengers, by a messenger who does not follow instructions, by a messenger gone and returned again."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.1.2"
msgid "araho rahosaññī,"
msgstr "Not in private, but perceiving it as private;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.1.3"
msgid "raho arahosaññī,"
msgstr "in private, but perceiving it as not private;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.1.4"
msgid "araho arahosaññī,"
msgstr "not in private, and perceiving it as not private;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.1.5"
msgid "raho rahosaññī"
msgstr "in private, and perceiving it as private."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.1.6"
msgid "kāyena saṃvaṇṇeti,"
msgstr "He praises by means of the body;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.1.7"
msgid "vācāya saṃvaṇṇeti,"
msgstr "he praises by means of speech;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.1.8"
msgid "kāyena vācāya saṃvaṇṇeti,"
msgstr "he praises by means of both the body and speech;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.1.9"
msgid "dūtena saṃvaṇṇeti,"
msgstr "he praises by means of a messenger;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.1.10"
msgid "lekhāya saṃvaṇṇeti,"
msgstr "he praises by means of writing."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.1.11"
msgid "opātaṃ apassenaṃ, upanikkhipanaṃ, bhesajjaṃ, rūpūpahāro, saddūpahāro, gandhūpahāro, rasūpahāro, ­phoṭṭhab­bū­pahāro, dhammūpahāro, ācikkhanā, anusāsanī, saṅketakammaṃ, nimitta­kammanti."
msgstr "A pit, a piece of furniture, placing near, medicine, arranging a sight, arranging a sound, arranging a smell, arranging a taste, arranging a touch, arranging a mental state, information, instruction, an action by appointment, making a sign."

#. HTML: </p><h4>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.0b"
msgid ""
msgstr "Exposition"

#. HTML: </h4><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc42, pts-cs-bu-pj3.4.2, pts-vp-en1.129, ms1V_417
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.1"
msgid "Sāmanti"
msgstr "Oneself:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.2"
msgid "sayaṃ hanati kāyena vā kāyapaṭi­bad­dhena vā nissaggiyena vā."
msgstr "one oneself kills by means of the body or by means of something attached to the body or by means of something released."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc43, ms1V_418
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.3"
msgid "Adhiṭṭhāyāti"
msgstr "Having resolved:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.4"
msgid "adhiṭṭhahitvā āṇāpeti—"
msgstr "having resolved, he tells someone,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.5"
msgid "“evaṃ vijjha, evaṃ pahara, evaṃ ghātehī”ti."
msgstr "“Hit thus, strike thus, kill thus.”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc44, pts-vp-pli3.75, ms1V_419
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.6"
msgid ""
msgstr "By messenger:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.7"
msgid "Bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ āṇāpeti—"
msgstr "If a monk tells a second monk,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.8"
msgid "“itthannāmaṃ jīvitā voropehī”ti,"
msgstr "“Kill so-and-so,”"

#. HTML: </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.9"
msgid "āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.10"
msgid "So taṃ maññamāno taṃ jīvitā voropeti,"
msgstr "If the second monk kills that person, thinking he is the one he was told to kill,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.11"
msgid "āpatti ubhinnaṃ pārājikassa."
msgstr "there is an offense entailing expulsion for both."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc45, ms1V_420
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.12"
msgid "Bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ āṇāpeti—"
msgstr "If a monk tells a second monk,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.13"
msgid "“itthannāmaṃ jīvitā voropehī”ti,"
msgstr "“Kill so-and-so,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.14"
msgid "āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.15"
msgid "So taṃ maññamāno aññaṃ jīvitā voropeti,"
msgstr "If the second monk kills someone else, thinking he is the one he was told to kill,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.16"
msgid "mūlaṭṭhassa anāpatti."
msgstr "there is no offense for the instigator,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.17"
msgid "Vadhakassa āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "but there is an offense entailing expulsion for the murderer."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc46, ms1V_421
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.18"
msgid "Bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ āṇāpeti—"
msgstr "If a monk tells a second monk,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.19"
msgid "“itthannāmaṃ jīvitā voropehī”ti,"
msgstr "“Kill so-and-so,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.20"
msgid "āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.21"
msgid "So aññaṃ maññamāno taṃ jīvitā voropeti,"
msgstr "If the second monk kills that person, thinking it is someone else than the one he was told to kill,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.22"
msgid "āpatti ubhinnaṃ pārājikassa."
msgstr "there is an offense entailing expulsion for both."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc47, ms1V_422
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.23"
msgid "Bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ āṇāpeti—"
msgstr "If a monk tells a second monk,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.24"
msgid "“itthannāmaṃ jīvitā voropehī”ti,"
msgstr "“Kill so-and-so,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.25"
msgid "āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.26"
msgid "So aññaṃ maññamāno aññaṃ jīvitā voropeti;"
msgstr "If the second monk kills someone else, thinking it is someone else than the one he was told to kill,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.27"
msgid "mūlaṭṭhassa anāpatti,"
msgstr "there is no offense for the instigator,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.28"
msgid "vadhakassa āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "but there is an offense entailing expulsion for the murderer."

#. HTML: </p><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc48, ms1V_423
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.29"
msgid ""
msgstr "By a series of messengers:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.30"
msgid "Bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ āṇāpeti—"
msgstr "If a monk tells a second monk,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.31"
msgid "“itthannāmassa pāvada—‘itthannāmo itthannāmassa pāvadatu—itthannāmo itthannāmaṃ jīvitā voropetū’”ti,"
msgstr "“Tell so-and-so to tell so-and-so to kill so-and-so,”"

#. HTML: </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.32"
msgid "āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.33"
msgid "So itarassa āroceti,"
msgstr "In telling the next person,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.34"
msgid "āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "there is an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.35"
msgid "Vadhako paṭiggaṇhāti,"
msgstr "If the murderer-to-be agrees,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.36"
msgid "mūlaṭṭhassa āpatti thullaccayassa."
msgstr "there is a serious offense for the instigator."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.37"
msgid "So taṃ jīvitā voropeti,"
msgstr "If he kills that person,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.38"
msgid "āpatti sabbesaṃ pārājikassa."
msgstr "there is an offense entailing expulsion for all of them."

#. HTML: </p><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc49, ms1V_424
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.39"
msgid ""
msgstr "By a messenger who does not follow instructions:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.40"
msgid "Bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ āṇāpeti—"
msgstr "If a monk tells a second monk,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.41"
msgid "“itthannāmassa pāvada—‘itthannāmo itthannāmassa pāvadatu—itthannāmo itthannāmaṃ jīvitā voropetū’”ti,"
msgstr "“Tell so-and-so to tell so-and-so to kill so-and-so,”"

#. HTML: </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.42"
msgid "āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.43"
msgid "So aññaṃ āṇāpeti,"
msgstr "If the second monk tells someone else than the one he was told to tell,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.44"
msgid "āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.45"
msgid "Vadhako paṭiggaṇhāti,"
msgstr "If the murderer-to-be agrees,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.46"
msgid "āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "there is an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.47"
msgid "So taṃ jīvitā voropeti,"
msgstr "If he kills that person,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.48"
msgid "mūlaṭṭhassa anāpatti;"
msgstr "there is no offense for the instigator,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.49"
msgid "āṇāpakassa ca vadhakassa ca āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "but there is an offense entailing expulsion for the messenger and for the murderer."

#. HTML: </p><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc50, ms1V_425
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.50"
msgid ""
msgstr "By a messenger gone and returned again:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.51"
msgid "Bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ āṇāpeti—"
msgstr "If a monk tells a second monk,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.52"
msgid "“itthannāmaṃ jīvitā voropehī”ti,"
msgstr "“Kill so-and-so,”"

#. HTML: </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.53"
msgid "āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. REF: pts-vp-en1.130
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.54"
msgid "So gantvā puna paccāgacchati—"
msgstr "He goes, but returns,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.55"
msgid "“nāhaṃ sakkomi taṃ jīvitā voropetun”ti."
msgstr "saying, “I wasn’t able to kill them.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.56"
msgid "So puna āṇāpeti—"
msgstr "If the first monk tells him again,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.57"
msgid "“yadā sakkosi tadā taṃ jīvitā voropehī”ti,"
msgstr "“When you’re able, then kill them,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.58"
msgid "āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.59"
msgid "So taṃ jīvitā voropeti,"
msgstr "If the second monk kills that person,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.60"
msgid "āpatti ubhinnaṃ pārājikassa."
msgstr "there is an offense entailing expulsion for both."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc51, ms1V_426
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.2.61"
msgid "Bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ āṇāpeti—"
