msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.10.19"
msgid "Saṅketakammaṃ nāma"
msgstr "An action by appointment:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
#. REF: pts-vp-en1.136
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.10.20"
msgid "saṅketaṃ karoti purebhattaṃ vā pacchābhattaṃ vā rattiṃ vā divā vā—"
msgstr "if a monk makes an appointment for before the meal or for after the meal, for the night or for the day, telling another person,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.10.21"
msgid "“tena saṅketena taṃ jīvitā voropehī”ti,"
msgstr "“Kill that person according to this appointment,”"

#. HTML: </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.10.22"
msgid "āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.10.23"
msgid "Tena saṅketena taṃ jīvitā voropeti,"
msgstr "If the other person kills that person according to that appointment,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.10.24"
msgid "āpatti ubhinnaṃ pārājikassa."
msgstr "there is an offense entailing expulsion for both."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.10.25"
msgid "Taṃ saṅketaṃ pure vā pacchā vā taṃ jīvitā voropeti,"
msgstr "If he kills him before or after the time of the appointment,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.10.26"
msgid "mūlaṭṭhassa anāpatti,"
msgstr "there is no offense for the instigator,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.10.27"
msgid "vadhakassa āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "but there is an offense entailing expulsion for the murderer."

#. HTML: </p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc73, ms1V_448
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.10.28"
msgid "Nimittakammaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Making a sign:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.10.29"
msgid "nimittaṃ karoti—"
msgstr "a monk makes a sign."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.10.30"
msgid "“akkhiṃ vā nikhaṇissāmi bhamukaṃ vā ukkhipissāmi sīsaṃ vā ukkhipissāmi, tena nimittena taṃ jīvitā voropehī”ti,"
msgstr "If he says to another person, “When I wink/raise my eyebrow/nod, at that sign kill that person,”"

#. HTML: </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.10.31"
msgid "āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.10.32"
msgid "Tena nimittena taṃ jīvitā voropeti,"
msgstr "If, at that sign, the other person kills that person,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.10.33"
msgid "āpatti ubhinnaṃ pārājikassa."
msgstr "there is an offense entailing expulsion for both."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.10.34"
msgid "Taṃ nimittaṃ pure vā pacchā vā taṃ jīvitā voropeti,"
msgstr "If he kills him before or after the sign,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.10.35"
msgid "mūlaṭṭhassa anāpatti,"
msgstr "there is no offense for the instigator,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.10.36"
msgid "vadhakassa āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "but there is an offense entailing expulsion for the murderer."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.11.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc74, pts-cs-bu-pj3.4.11, ms1V_449
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.11.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.11.2"
msgid "asañcicca"
msgstr "if it is unintentional;"

#. VAR: ajānantassa namara­ṇādhip­pāyassa ummattakassa → ummattakassa khittacittassa vedanaṭṭassa (bj, s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.11.3"
msgid "ajānantassa"
msgstr "if he does not know;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.11.4"
msgid "namara­ṇādhip­pāyassa"
msgstr "if he is not aiming at death;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.11.5"
msgid "ummattakassa"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.11.6"
msgid "ādi­kammi­kas­sāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
#. REF: sc75, ms1V_450
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.11.7"
msgid "Manus­savig­gaha­pā­rāji­kamhi paṭha­ma­bhā­ṇavāro niṭṭhito."
msgstr "The first section on expulsion in relation to human beings is finished."

#. HTML: </p><hr><h5>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.11.8"
msgid "3.1. Vinīta­vatthu­uddāna­gāthā"
msgstr "Case rulings mnemonic list"

#. HTML: </h5><div class="uddana"><p>
#. REF: sc76, pts-vp-pli3.79, ms1V_451
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.11.9"
msgid "Saṃvaṇṇanā nisīdanto,"
msgstr "Praising, sitting down,"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.11.10"
msgid "musalo­duk­kha­lena ca;"
msgstr "And with pestle, with mortar;"

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: Vuḍḍha­pabba­ji­tā­bhisanno → buddha­pabba­jitā satta (bj) | vuḍḍha­pabba­jitā santo (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.11.11"
msgid "Vuḍḍha­pabba­ji­tā­bhisanno,"
msgstr "Gone forth when old, flowing out,"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.11.12"
msgid "agga­vī­maṃ­sa­nā­visaṃ."
msgstr "First, experimental poison."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc77, pts-vp-en1.137, ms1V_452
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.11.13"
msgid "Tayo ca vatthukammehi,"
msgstr "And three with making sites,"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.11.14"
msgid "iṭṭhakāhipare tayo;"
msgstr "Another three with bricks;"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.11.15"
msgid "Vāsī gopānasī ceva,"
msgstr "An machete, and a rafter,"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.11.16"
msgid "aṭṭakotaraṇaṃ pati."
msgstr "A elevated platform, coming down, fell down."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc78, ms1V_453
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.11.17"
msgid "Sedaṃ natthuñca sambāho,"
msgstr "Sweating, and nose treatment, massage,"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.11.18"
msgid "nhāpanab­bhañ­ja­nena ca;"
msgstr "By bathing, and by smearing;"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.11.19"
msgid "Uṭṭhāpento nipātento,"
msgstr "Making get up, making lie down,"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.11.20"
msgid "annapānena māraṇaṃ."
msgstr "Death through food, through drink."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc79, ms1V_454
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.11.21"
msgid "Jāragabbho sapattī ca,"
msgstr "Child by a lover, and co-wives,"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.11.22"
msgid "mātā puttaṃ ubho vadhi;"
msgstr "Mother, child, he killed both;"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.11.23"
msgid "Ubho na miyyare maddā,"
msgstr "He killed neither, crushing,"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.11.24"
msgid "tāpaṃ vañjhā vijāyinī."
msgstr "Heating, barren, fertile."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc80, ms1V_455
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.11.25"
msgid "Patodaṃ niggahe yakkho,"
msgstr "Tickling, in taking hold of, a spirit,"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.11.26"
msgid "vāḷayakkhañca pāhiṇi;"
msgstr "Wild animals, and spirits, sent;"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.11.27"
msgid "Taṃ maññamāno pahari,"
msgstr "Thinking it was him, he gave a blow,"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.11.28"
msgid "saggañca nirayaṃ bhaṇe."
msgstr "In talking about heaven, and about hell."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc81, ms1V_456
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.11.29"
msgid "Āḷaviyā tayo rukkhā,"
msgstr "Three trees at Āḷavī,"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.11.30"
msgid "dāyehi apare tayo;"
msgstr "Three others with forest groves;"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.11.31"
msgid "Mā kilamesi na tuyhaṃ,"
msgstr "Do not torture, not as you,"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:4.11.32"
msgid "takkaṃ sovīrakena cāti."
msgstr "Buttermilk, and salty medicine."

#. HTML: </p></div><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.1.0"
msgid "3.2. Vinītavatthu"
msgstr "Case details"

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: sc82, pts-cs-bu-pj3.5.1, ms1V_457
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.1.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu gilāno hoti."
msgstr "On one occasion a certain monk was sick."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.1.2"
msgid "Tassa bhikkhū kāruññena maraṇavaṇṇaṃ saṃvaṇṇesuṃ."
msgstr "Feeling compassion, the monks praised death to him."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.1.3"
msgid "So bhikkhu kālamakāsi."
msgstr "He died."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.1.4"
msgid "Tesaṃ kukkuccaṃ ahosi “bhagavatā sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ, kacci nu kho mayaṃ pārājikaṃ āpattiṃ āpannā”ti?"
msgstr "They became remorseful and said, “Could it be that we’ve committed an offense entailing expulsion?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.1.5"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "They told the Master,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.1.6"
msgid "“Āpattiṃ tumhe, bhikkhave, āpannā pārājikan”ti. #1"
msgstr " and he said, “You have committed an offense entailing expulsion.”"

#. HTML: </p><hr><p>
#. REF: sc83, pts-cs-bu-pj3.5.2, ms1V_458
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.2.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aññataro piṇḍacāriko bhikkhu pīṭhake pilotikāya paṭicchannaṃ dārakaṃ nisīdanto ottharitvā māresi."
msgstr "On one occasion a monk who was an alms-collector sat down on a bench, crushing a boy who was concealed by a piece of cloth. The boy died."

#. REF: pts-vp-en1.138
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.2.2"
msgid "Tassa kukkuccaṃ ahosi “bhagavatā sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ, kacci nu kho ahaṃ pārājikaṃ āpattiṃ āpanno”ti?"
msgstr "The monk became remorseful and thought, “Could it be that I’ve committed an offense entailing expulsion?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.2.3"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesi."
msgstr "He told the Master, and the Master said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.2.4"
msgid "“Anāpatti, bhikkhu, pārājikassa."
msgstr "“There’s no offense entailing expulsion."

#. HTML: <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.2.5"
msgid "Na ca, bhikkhave, appa­ṭi­vek­khitvā āsane nisīditabbaṃ;"
msgstr "But you should not sit down on a seat without checking it."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.2.6"
msgid "yo nisīdeyya,"
msgstr "If you do,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.2.7"
msgid "āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti. #2"
msgstr "you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”"

#. HTML: </span> </p><hr><p>
#. REF: sc84, pts-cs-bu-pj3.5.3, ms1V_459
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.3.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu bhattagge antaraghare āsanaṃ paññapento musale ussite ekaṃ musalaṃ aggahesi."
msgstr "On one occasion a monk was preparing a seat in a dining hall in an inhabited area."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.3.2"
msgid "Dutiyo musalo paripatitvā aññatarassa dārakassa matthake avatthāsi."
msgstr "When he took hold of a pestle high up, a second pestle fell down, hitting a boy,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.3.3"
msgid "So kālamakāsi."
msgstr "who then died."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.3.4"
msgid "Tassa kukkuccaṃ ahosi … pe …"
msgstr "The monk became remorseful …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.3.5"
msgid "“kiṃcitto tvaṃ, bhikkhū”ti?"
msgstr "“What was your intention?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.3.6"
msgid "“Asañcicca ahaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“I didn’t intend it, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.3.7"
msgid "“Anāpatti, bhikkhu, asañciccā”ti. #3"
msgstr "“There’s no offense when it’s unintentional.”"

#. HTML: </p><hr><p>
#. REF: sc85, ms1V_460
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.3.8"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu bhattagge antaraghare āsanaṃ paññapento uduk­kha­la­bhaṇḍi­kaṃ akkamitvā pavaṭṭesi."
msgstr "On one occasion a monk was preparing a seat in a dining hall in an inhabited area. He stepped on the implements belonging to a mortar."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.3.9"
msgid "Aññataraṃ dārakaṃ ottharitvā māresi."
msgstr "They fell and hit a boy, who then died."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.3.10"
msgid "Tassa kukkuccaṃ ahosi … pe …"
msgstr "The monk became remorseful …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.3.11"
msgid "“anāpatti, bhikkhu, asañciccā”ti. #4"
msgstr "“There’s no offense when it’s unintentional.”"

#. HTML: </p><hr><p>
#. REF: sc86, pts-cs-bu-pj3.5.4, ms1V_461
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.4.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena pitāputtā bhikkhūsu pabbajitā honti."
msgstr "At one time there was a father and son who had gone forth with the monks."

# NOTE: “For a certain event” is not found in the Pali, but has been added to make the Pali idiom clearer.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.4.2"
msgid "Kāle ārocite putto pitaraṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "When the time was announced for a certain event, the son said to his father, "

#. REF: pts-vp-en1.139
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.4.3"
msgid "“gaccha, bhante, saṃgho taṃ patimānetī”ti piṭṭhiyaṃ gahetvā paṇāmesi."
msgstr "“Go, Venerable, the Order is waiting for you,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.4.4"
msgid "piṭṭhiyaṃ gahetvā paṇāmesi."
msgstr "and seizing him by the back, he pushed him."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.4.5"
msgid "So papatitvā kālamakāsi."
msgstr "The father fell and died."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.4.6"
msgid "Tassa kukkuccaṃ ahosi … pe …"
msgstr "The son became remorseful …"

#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.80
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.4.7"
msgid "“kiṃcitto tvaṃ, bhikkhū”ti?"
msgstr "“What was your intention?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.4.8"
msgid "“Nāhaṃ, bhagavā, maraṇādhippāyo”ti."
msgstr "“I didn’t mean to kill him, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.4.9"
msgid "“Anāpatti, bhikkhu, ­namara­ṇādhip­pāyassā”ti. #5"
msgstr "“There’s no offense for one who is not aiming at death."

#. HTML: </p><hr><p>
#. REF: sc87, ms1V_462
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.4.10"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena pitāputtā bhikkhūsu pabbajitā honti."
msgstr "At one time there was a father and son who had gone forth with the monks."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.4.11"
msgid "Kāle ārocite putto pitaraṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "When the time was announced for a certain event, the son said to his father,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.4.12"
msgid "“gaccha, bhante, saṃgho taṃ patimānetī”ti"
msgstr "“Go, Venerable, the Order is waiting for you,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.4.13"
msgid "maraṇādhippāyo piṭṭhiyaṃ gahetvā paṇāmesi."
msgstr "and meaning to kill him, he seized him by the back and pushed him."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.4.14"
msgid "So papatitvā kālamakāsi."
msgstr "The father fell and died."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.4.15"
msgid "Tassa kukkuccaṃ ahosi … pe …"
msgstr "The son became remorseful …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.4.16"
msgid "“āpattiṃ tvaṃ, bhikkhu, āpanno pārājikan”ti. #6"
msgstr "“You have committed an offense entailing expulsion.”"

#. HTML: </p><hr><p>
#. REF: sc88, ms1V_463
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.4.17"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena pitāputtā bhikkhūsu pabbajitā honti."
msgstr "At one time there was a father and son who had gone forth with the monks."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.4.18"
msgid "Kāle ārocite putto pitaraṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "When the time was announced for a certain event, the son said to his father,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.4.19"
msgid "“gaccha, bhante, saṃgho taṃ patimānetī”ti"
msgstr "“Go, Venerable, the Order is waiting for you,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.4.20"
msgid "maraṇādhippāyo piṭṭhiyaṃ gahetvā paṇāmesi."
msgstr "and meaning to kill him, he seized him by the back and pushed him."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.4.21"
msgid "So papatitvā na kālamakāsi."
msgstr "The father fell, but did not die."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.4.22"
msgid "Tassa kukkuccaṃ ahosi … pe …"
msgstr "The son became remorseful …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.4.23"
msgid "“anāpatti, bhikkhu, pārājikassa;"
msgstr "“There’s no offense entailing expulsion,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.4.24"
msgid "āpatti thullaccayassā”ti. #7"
msgstr "but there’s a serious offense.”"

#. HTML: </p><hr><p>
#. REF: sc89, pts-cs-bu-pj3.5.5, ms1V_464
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.5.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aññatarassa bhikkhuno bhuñjantassa maṃsaṃ kaṇṭhe vilaggaṃ hoti."
msgstr "On one occasion, while a monk was eating, some meat got stuck in his throat."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.5.2"
msgid "Aññataro bhikkhu tassa bhikkhuno gīvāyaṃ pahāraṃ adāsi."
msgstr "A second monk hit him on the neck."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.5.3"
msgid "Salohitaṃ maṃsaṃ pati."
msgstr "The meat came out together with blood,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.5.4"
msgid "So bhikkhu kālamakāsi."
msgstr "and the monk died."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.5.5"
msgid "Tassa kukkuccaṃ ahosi … pe …"
msgstr "The second monk became remorseful …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.5.6"
msgid "“anāpatti, bhikkhu, ­namara­ṇādhip­pāyassā”ti. #8"
msgstr "“There’s no offense for one who is not aiming at death.”"

#. HTML: </p><hr><p>
#. REF: sc90, ms1V_465
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.5.7"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aññatarassa bhikkhuno bhuñjantassa maṃsaṃ kaṇṭhe vilaggaṃ hoti."
msgstr "On one occasion, while a monk was eating, some meat got stuck in his throat."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.5.8"
msgid "Aññataro bhikkhu maraṇādhippāyo tassa bhikkhuno gīvāyaṃ pahāraṃ adāsi."
msgstr "A second monk, meaning to kill him, hit him on the neck."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj3:5.5.9"
msgid "Salohitaṃ maṃsaṃ pati."
msgstr "The meat came out together with blood,"

